hip mapping, including 'BIOMARKER TESTING (part of MGPT) → Testing Results' and 'CONSIDER BIOMARKER TESTING (part of MGPT) → Testing Results,' provides clarity and reduces risk of omission in testing, a critical aspect of modern NSCLC care [Data: Entities (128, 129, 130, 131, 132); Relationships (294, 295, 296, 297, 289)].\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"summary\": \"Structured Nature of the Protocols Reflects Best Practices and Legal Compliance\",\n      \"explanation\": \"The detailed, stepwise nature of the relationships among entities in these protocols mirrors current best clinical practices and the need for legal compliance when treating NSCLC. The defined transitions between workup steps, decision points, and recommended actions indicate adherence to consensus guidelines (e.g., NCCN), providing a defensible basis for clinical decisions and meeting regulatory requirements for evidence-based care in oncology [Data: Entities (49, 124, 126); Relationships (106, 110, 114, 116, 117, 282, 289, 290, 291, 292, 294, 295, 296, 297, +more)].\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"summary\": \"Comprehensive Systemic Therapy Consideration for N2–3 and Advanced/Metastatic NSCLC\",\n      \"explanation\": \"Where N2–3 nodal involvement or metastatic spread is established, the protocol mandates escalation to advanced/metastatic pathways (NSCL-19), ensuring prompt consideration of systemic therapies including chemotherapy, targeted treatments, and immunotherapies. The pathway helps avoid unnecessary surgical interventions in non-curative settings, improving patient safety and directing resources appropriately [Data: Entities (60, 124, 125); Relationships (117, 282)].\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"summary\": \"Explicit Links Between Histologic Subtype and Testing, Supporting Precision Medicine\",\n      \"explanation\": \"The protocols clearly map which histologic subtypes (adenocarcinoma, large cell, squamous cell carcinoma) should undergo specific biomarker panels, tailoring the diagnostic and ther